 AN its quest to provide tailor-made solutions for small and medium enterprises (SMEs),  leading ICT firm, MTN Nigeria supported the recently concluded SME Clinic facilitated by Techpoint Africa held at the National Theatre, Iganmu, Lagos. The SME Clinic was developed to assist Nigerian start-ups scale their businesses leveraging the power of technology. Damilola Runsewe, Senior Manager, SME Segment Management, Enterprise Business Unit (EBU), MTN Nigeria, presented various solutions created by the company to assist businesses in Nigeria. He explained the benefits of products like the Hynetflex and CallAssists help with the growth of small businesses. Runsewe reiterated on MTN’s continued support for businesses in the country – “It’s 2020 and the business world is more competitive than ever. With our understanding of the policies, new developments, the rapid digitization of businesses in Nigeria and the rest of the world, we have decided to take necessary steps in pulling others along.  We are always stronger together and all the businesses you see here form vital parts of the building blocks of our economy.” Other speakers, who shared insights on tools and tips to boost businesses include Tolulope Akinyele Google Partners Lead, Nigeria; Tope Olofin, Founder/CEO NaturaGlow by Abby Jo; Oladimeji Olutoye MD/Lead Consultant, DE Maven Advisory and Consulting Ltd; Ayoade Akinfemiwa Agency Relationship Manager;  Uwem Uwemakpan Lagos Chapter Director, Startupgrind; Debbie Akwara Founder/Principal Customer Experience Consultant and Peter ‘PeteSocial’ Nwabuoku Head of Business Development & Digital at Luzo DN & Media Ltd. 